    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Order of array data in memory\n",
        "\n",
        "* <font color=\"red\">Multidimensional arrays are stored as contiguous data in memory</font>. $~$Consider the case of a two-dimensional array, $~$containing rows and columns: $~$One possible way to store this array as a consecutive sequence of values is to store the rows after each other, and another equally valid approach is to store the columns one after another\n",
        "\n",
        "* The former is called <font color=\"green\">row-major format</font> and the latter is <font color=\"green\">column-major format</font>. Whether to use row-major or column-major is a matter of conventions, and the **row-major format** is used for example in the **C** programming language, and **Fortran** uses the **column-major format**\n",
        "\n",
        "* A `numpy` array can be specified to be stored in row-major format, using the keyword argument `order='C'`, and column-major format, using the keyword argument `order='F'`, when the array is created or reshaped. <font color=\"blue\">The default format is *row-major*</font> \n",
        "\n",
        "* In general, the `numpy` array attribute `ndarray.strides` defines exactly how this mapping is done. The `strides` attribute is a tuple of the same length as the number of axes (dimensions) of the array. Each value in `strides` is the factor by which the index for the corresponding axis is multiplied when calculating the *memory offset (in bytes)* for a given index expression\n"
      ],
      "id": "0246cc19"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]], dtype=np.int32)\n",
        "data"
      ],
      "id": "059f396e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data.strides"
      ],
      "id": "6d8e1e9f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]], dtype=np.int32, order='F')\n",
        "data"
      ],
      "id": "0ceadefe",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data.strides"
      ],
      "id": "188ffa6d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Creating arrays\n",
        "\n",
        "### Arrays created from lists and other array-like objects\n"
      ],
      "id": "850cfb4d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4])\n",
        "data.ndim, data.shape"
      ],
      "id": "9847290b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.array(((1, 2), (3, 4)))\n",
        "data.ndim, data.shape"
      ],
      "id": "9da65829",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Arrays filled with constant values\n"
      ],
      "id": "4bf76fa4"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.zeros((2, 3))"
      ],
      "id": "bf6513fd",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.ones(4)\n",
        "data, data.dtype"
      ],
      "id": "cc98086c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "5.4 * np.ones(10)"
      ],
      "id": "702a0c9f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.full(10, 5.4) # slightly more efficient"
      ],
      "id": "affa75ae",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x1 = np.empty(5)\n",
        "x1.fill(3.0)\n",
        "x1"
      ],
      "id": "42e5f773",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Arrays filled with incremental sequences\n"
      ],
      "id": "23a6757a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.arange(0, 11, 1)"
      ],
      "id": "0186b31d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.linspace(0, 10, 11)  # generally recommended"
      ],
      "id": "fdf751e7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Arrays filled with logarithmic sequences\n"
      ],
      "id": "a8c56401"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.logspace(0, 2, 10)  # 5 data points between 10**0=1 to 10**2=100"
      ],
      "id": "5a05fa4f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Mesh grid arrays\n"
      ],
      "id": "b0594652"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = np.array([-1, 0, 1])\n",
        "y = np.array([-2, 0, 2])\n",
        "\n",
        "X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)"
      ],
      "id": "298ddddb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "X"
      ],
      "id": "becbbce3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Y"
      ],
      "id": "ec239c1d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Z = (X + Y)**2\n",
        "Z"
      ],
      "id": "3378f1c3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Creating uninitialized arrays\n"
      ],
      "id": "2931541a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.empty(3, dtype=float)"
      ],
      "id": "45421065",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Creating arrays with properties of other arrays\n"
      ],
      "id": "c211611f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def f(x):    \n",
        "    y = np.ones_like(x)    # compute with x and y    \n",
        "    return y\n",
        "\n",
        "x = np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]])\n",
        "y = f(x)\n",
        "y"
      ],
      "id": "ecc56a42",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Creating matrix arrays\n"
      ],
      "id": "9a9e8be7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.identity(4)"
      ],
      "id": "ab4240f4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.eye(4, k=1)"
      ],
      "id": "d268fa01",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.eye(4, k=-1)"
      ],
      "id": "dbd404a2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.diag(np.arange(0, 20, 5))"
      ],
      "id": "94b4824b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Indexing and slicing\n",
        "\n",
        "### One-dimensional arrays\n"
      ],
      "id": "0764b92c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a = np.arange(0, 11)\n",
        "a"
      ],
      "id": "8b1ddf54",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[0]"
      ],
      "id": "1867da88",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[-1]"
      ],
      "id": "65cad8bb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[4]"
      ],
      "id": "08668c75",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "1a3fcbe7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[1:-1]"
      ],
      "id": "959e59d5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[1:-1:2]"
      ],
      "id": "9a2bfb7f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "8df49af4"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[:5]"
      ],
      "id": "747854a5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[-5:]"
      ],
      "id": "6fe3b606",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a[::-2]"
      ],
      "id": "4aff87e6",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Multidimensional arrays\n"
      ],
      "id": "e1cd601a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f = lambda m, n: n + 10*m"
      ],
      "id": "671a179f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# please search for numpy.fromfunction at google\n",
        "A = np.fromfunction(f, (6, 6), dtype=int)\n",
        "A  "
      ],
      "id": "7ac731f9",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[:, 1]  # the second column"
      ],
      "id": "1e3a74b6",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[1, :]  # the second row"
      ],
      "id": "8ba5ea7b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[:3, :3]"
      ],
      "id": "fa1f8169",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[3:, :3]"
      ],
      "id": "fd784aab",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[::2, ::2]"
      ],
      "id": "3222a67f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[1::2, 1::3]"
      ],
      "id": "6c1c2114",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Views\n",
        "\n",
        "* Subarrays that are extracted from arrays using slice operations are **alternative views** of the same underlying array data. That is, $~$they are arrays that refer to the same data in memory as the original array, $~$but with a different `strides` configuration\n",
        "\n",
        "* When elements in a view are assigned new values, $~$the values of the original\n",
        "array are therefore also updated. For example,\n"
      ],
      "id": "3c20f27b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "B = A[1:5, 1:5]\n",
        "B"
      ],
      "id": "c7d4034f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "B[:, :] = 0\n",
        "A"
      ],
      "id": "cc6c2eda",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "* When a copy rather than a view is needed, the view can be copied explicitly by using the `copy` method of the `ndarray` instance\n"
      ],
      "id": "d3d1d0d5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "C = B[1:3, 1:3].copy()\n",
        "C"
      ],
      "id": "0d585762",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "C[:, :] = 1\n",
        "C"
      ],
      "id": "84c32134",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "B"
      ],
      "id": "5a260ac3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Fancy indexing and boolean-valued indexing\n"
      ],
      "id": "56e47a1a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A = np.linspace(0, 1, 11)\n",
        "A"
      ],
      "id": "43722030",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[np.array([0, 2, 4])]"
      ],
      "id": "f17491c7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[[0, 2, 4]]"
      ],
      "id": "6be4f7d5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "dfda7c69"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A > 0.5"
      ],
      "id": "f241f327",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[A > 0.5]"
      ],
      "id": "8300f018",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "* Unlike arrays created by using slices, $~$**the arrays returned using fancy indexing and Boolean-valued\n",
        "indexing are not views**, $~$but rather new independent arrays\n"
      ],
      "id": "5834a679"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A = np.arange(10)\n",
        "indices = [2, 4, 6]"
      ],
      "id": "d1a8ce72",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "B = A[indices]"
      ],
      "id": "14ec858a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "B[0] = -1\n",
        "A"
      ],
      "id": "f1c2f647",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[indices] = -1\n",
        "A"
      ],
      "id": "c640dc0b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "73aa78e1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A = np.arange(10)"
      ],
      "id": "f30296e6",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "B = A[A > 5]"
      ],
      "id": "a6978d02",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "B[0] = -1\n",
        "A"
      ],
      "id": "e89dd8bc",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A[A > 5] = -1\n",
        "A"
      ],
      "id": "28d7e638",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Summery\n"
      ],
      "id": "0b2c9a7c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), ':, :')"
      ],
      "id": "e46604d1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '0')"
      ],
      "id": "49af4c44",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '1, :')"
      ],
      "id": "4b9dea6f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), ':, 2')"
      ],
      "id": "dcf8e17c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "e95f9778"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '0:2, 0:2')"
      ],
      "id": "5f895ba1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '0:2, 2:4')"
      ],
      "id": "e3d15408",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '::2, ::2')"
      ],
      "id": "6dd2ace5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '1::2, 1::2')"
      ],
      "id": "b37a9f6d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), ':, [0, 3]')"
      ],
      "id": "c47c58d5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '[1, 3], [0, 3]')"
      ],
      "id": "fe234ee8",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), ':, [False, True, True, False]')"
      ],
      "id": "1a8e492c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "show_array((4, 4), '1:3, [False, True, True, False]')"
      ],
      "id": "5435f664",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Reshaping and resizing\n",
        "\n",
        "* Reshaping an array does not require modifying the underlying array data; it only changes in how the data is interpreted, by redefining the array’s strides attribute\n"
      ],
      "id": "1ba2895d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])\n",
        "data1 = np.reshape(data, (1, 4))\n",
        "data1"
      ],
      "id": "36696c9c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data1[0, 1] = -1\n",
        "data"
      ],
      "id": "b35fe2c2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data2 = data.reshape(4)\n",
        "data2"
      ],
      "id": "15e1e55a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data2[1] = -2\n",
        "data"
      ],
      "id": "c3426728",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "4e9e350f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])\n",
        "data1 = np.ravel(data)\n",
        "data1"
      ],
      "id": "5a98a6eb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data1[0] = -1\n",
        "data"
      ],
      "id": "9ac2746d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "* The `ndarray` method `flatten` perform the same function, $~$but\n",
        "returns a **copy** instead of a view\n"
      ],
      "id": "bf8adf84"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data2 = data.flatten()\n",
        "data2"
      ],
      "id": "a6772db5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data2[0] = -2\n",
        "data"
      ],
      "id": "54247d25",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "e8bfb7c0"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "data = np.arange(0, 5)\n",
        "data.shape"
      ],
      "id": "f8eb5b03",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "column = data[:, np.newaxis]\n",
        "column"
      ],
      "id": "aeab7834",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "column.shape"
      ],
      "id": "4f0a83f5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "row = data[np.newaxis, :]\n",
        "row"
      ],
      "id": "9ac9f138",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "row.shape"
      ],
      "id": "f61c7b85",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "row[0, 0] = -1\n",
        "data"
      ],
      "id": "d2a65d56",
      "execution_count": null,
